HEADWORD: Stilpnomelane
<hw>Stilp*nom"e*lane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>stilpno`s</grk> shining + <grk>me`las</grk>, <grk>-anos</grk>,
black.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A black or greenish black mineral
occurring in foliated flates, also in velvety bronze-colored
incrustations. It is a hydrous silicate of iron and alumina.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

